Package com.pauliankline.floopyconnector

Class GameController

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pauliankline.floopyconnector.GameController
  • public abstract class GameController
extends Object
    This class controls the higher level logic like going through the list of heros and calling their gameTickAction and filtering out the dead ones before next gameTick.

    pauli

      • createHeroes

        public abstract ArrayList<BaseHero> createHeroes​(GameBoard gb,
                                                 int quantity)
        This method will get called to place heroes randomly throughout the given gameboard, storing each hero's location in their own location property. Note that GameBoard squares also need to store the heroes standing on them! You need to set those as well!
        Parameters:
        board - The board to be ammended with Heroes.
        quantity - how many heroes will be generated.

      • mkGameBoard

        public abstract GameBoard mkGameBoard()
        Implementation of this method need to create a game board of your desired default size. It is easy enough to make a new GameBoard instance, but the world also needs to be populated with items!
